Defendant in court with Attorney Jon Oliver Helland.  Shaun W O'Connell appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Carlos S London in court with attorney Jon Oliver Helland. Reporter:  Phil Harrelson - Ctrm w/o final jury panel present.  15TR5264 defendant pleas no contest to.  15TR5262 will be settled via court trial.  Ct and counsel discussed preliminary jury instructions. Atty Helland objects to juror note taking.  Ct. overrules objection. Parties stipulate on chain of evidence of blood transport. Atty Helland and ADA OConnell discuss changes to exhibit 1 transcript of video audio. Ex. 1-5 marked prior to start of trial for day.
Final jury panel present in ctrm @ 9:23 am. Final jury panel sworn by clerk. Preliminary instructions given by ct. 
Opening Stmt by ADA OConnell @ 9:38 am. Opening Stmt by Atty Helland @ 9:44 am.
States Case
Thomas Keefe, Dane County Sheriffs Office Deputy, duly sworn & testifies. Direct by ADA OConnell.  ADA OConnell moves ex 2&3 into evidence. No objection by Atty Helland. Ex. 2&3 recd by ct. Cross by Atty. Helland. Re-direct by ADA OConnell. 
Jury excused @ 10:48 am for break. Ct. receives ex. 1 as parties stipulated to the transcript of video. Ct. recesses @ 10:50 am. Ct. reconvenes @ 11:15 am.
Ct. reads stipulation re chain of custody to the jury per ADA OConnells request. 
Molly Ross, toxicologist, duly sworn & testifies.  Direct by ADA OConnell. ADA OConnell moves ex 4&5 into evidence.  No objection by Atty Helland. Ex. 4,5 recd by ct. Cross by Atty Helland. Redirect by ADA OConnell. 
State rests @ 11:32 am. Jury excused for short break @ 11:34 am. Atty Helland indicates defendant wants to testify.  Ct. has colloquy with defendant regarding that. Defendant still indicates he wants to testify. Jury back in ctrm @ 11:46 am
Defenses Case 
Carlos London, duly sworn & testifies.  Direct by Atty Helland. Cross by ADA OConnell. Redirect by Atty Helland. 
Jury excused @ 12:19 pm.  Outside presence of jury Atty Helland argues to allow hearsay testimony that will be presented from defendants brother after lunch break.  No objection from ADA OConnell. ADA OConnell makes request for instruction.  Atty Helland does not object.  Ct. recesses @ 12:24 pm.
Ct reconvenes @ 1:30 pm. 
Christopher London, duly sworn & testifies.  Direct by Atty Helland.  Cross by ADA OConnell. 
Defense rests @ 1:47 pm.  State has no rebuttal evidence. 
Jury excused for break @ 1:49.  Outside presence of jury Jury instruction conference held btwn Ct. and counsel.  Jury present in ctrm @ 2:30 pm. Final instructions read to jury by ct. 
Closing Argument by ADA OConnell.  Closing Argument by Atty Helland. Rebuttal Argument by ADA OConnell. 
Juror #8 chosen as alternate. & excused @ 3:20 pm. Final instructions read by the Ct.  Baliff, duly sworn by clerk. Jury deliberations begin @ 3:25 pm.  Ct. rules that exhibits 3,4&5 can go back to jury if they ask for exhibits.  No objection by counsel. 
Argument by counsel on 15TR5262.  Ct. finds that burden of proof has not been met and orders 15TR5262 dismissed. Parties stipulate to fine amount on 15TR5264 which defendant entered plea of no contest to. 
In ctrm. outside presence of jury @ 4:06 pm to address jury question #1. Parties agree on answer to question #1. 
In ctrm. outside presence of jury @ 5:29 pm to address jury question #2.  Parties agree on answer to question #2. 
Ct. notified by Bailiff that jury has reached verdict @ 6:20 pm; counsel notified by clerk.  Jury present in ctrm @ 6:25 pm
Verdicts read by Ct as follows:  
	Ct 1:  NOT GUILTY
	Ct 2:  NOT GUILTY 
Jury polled by ct. collectively as a group.  Jury excused by ct. @ 6:29 pm.
Atty Hellend moves for judgment on verdict.  Ct. grants motion and enters judgment of acquittal. Case is dismissed.
